AZA Technology
An AZA Tech SAG project

Collaborative technology projects for AZA institutions

The Technology Scientific Advisory Group (SAG) empowers AZA institutions with technology best practices, data stewardship, and innovative solutions—advancing conservation, education, research, animal care, and visitor experiences.

Learn more about the Tech SAG Start working together.

What is this page?

This is the landing page for the technology projects and resources we're developing in the Tech SAG and around the AZA.

Conservation & Research

Data pipelines and open datasets powering conservation science and research insights.

Education & Visitor Experience

Interactive tools, APIs, and content systems that enrich learning and inspire guests.

Animal Care

Evidence-based technology for welfare tracking, husbandry planning, and operations.

Built to share

  • Clear goals and lightweight, common-sense governance.
  • Welcoming, documentation-first workflows.
  • Inclusive communities and transparent communication.
  • Practical plans for sustainable projects.
  • Prioritize security, data stewardship, and responsible innovation.
  • Measure impact across conservation, education, and guest engagement.
